What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Too many feedback requirements--I found them unnecessary and unhelpful to my final product. I would eliminate them entirely.

It's the senior essay with your preferred advisor! A great opportunity to apply what you have learned in the four years. The workshops were a bit helpful but maybe if there were multiple grad students helping, students can have a bit more direct help. Overall, good.

I would recommend doing your senior essay this way. Doing it as part of a course creates more work while leading you to pay less attention to your senior essay. Writing a thesis is a quintessential college experience, and I would recommend giving it the attention it deserves by doing the separate seminar.
The senior essay is fine. I would not wish the major on anyone, but if you're reading this course evaluation it is surely too late for you.
